    <briefdescription>
<para>Scheduler that evaluates spawn rules and produces spawn plans. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1scheduling_1_1SpawnScheduler" kindref="compound">SpawnScheduler</ref> is the central coordinator for rule-based spawning. It maintains a collection of spawn rules, evaluates them each frame, and produces <ref refid="structhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1scheduling_1_1ScheduledSpawnPlan" kindref="compound">ScheduledSpawnPlan</ref> instances for rules whose conditions are met.</para>
<para>## Workflow</para>
<para>1. **Registration:** Rules are added via `addRule()` with their profile ID 2. **Evaluation:** `evaluate()` is called each frame by GameObjectSpawnSystem 3. **Scheduling:** Rules that pass conditions produce ScheduledSpawnPlans 4. **Draining:** `drainScheduledPlans()` returns and clears pending plans 5. **Commit:** `commit()` is called when spawns complete to update state</para>
<para>Example: ```cpp <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1spawn_1_1scheduling_1_1SpawnScheduler" kindref="compound">SpawnScheduler</ref> scheduler; scheduler.addRule(enemyProfileId, std::make_unique&lt;TimerSpawnRule&gt;( ruleId, 2.0f, 3 // Every 2s, spawn 3 ));</para>
<para>// In game loop scheduler.evaluate(updateContext); auto plans = scheduler.drainScheduledPlans(); ```</para>
